trans-unit.source: Represents a security token provider that provides <xref href="System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken"></xref> security tokens for a SOAP message sender.
trans-unit.target: Representa um provedor de token de segurança que fornece <xref href="System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken"> </xref> tokens de segurança para um SOAP remetente da mensagem.

trans-unit.source: In most instances the KerberosSecurityTokenProvider class doesn't need to be called directly, as it is called when a client sends a SOAP message that requires a <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken> security token.
trans-unit.target: Na maioria dos casos de KerberosSecurityTokenProvider classe não precisa ser chamado diretamente, como ele é chamado quando um cliente envia uma mensagem SOAP que requer um <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>token de segurança.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>

trans-unit.source: Specifically, a client specifies the type of security token needed using the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ClientCredentials> class and the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ClientCredentials> class calls the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A> method to get a security token.
trans-unit.target: Especificamente, um cliente especifica o tipo de segurança token necessário usando o <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ClientCredentials>classe e o <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ClientCredentials>classe chama o <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A>método para obter um token de segurança.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A> </xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ClientCredentials> </xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ClientCredentials>

trans-unit.source: When the security token needed is a <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken> security token, the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A> method calls the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.KerberosSecurityTokenProvider.GetTokenCore%28System.TimeSpan%29> method.
trans-unit.target: Quando o token de segurança necessário é um <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>do token de segurança a <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A>chamadas de método de <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.KerberosSecurityTokenProvider.GetTokenCore%28System.TimeSpan%29>método.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.KerberosSecurityTokenProvider.GetTokenCore%28System.TimeSpan%29> </xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A> </xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A> method is called by the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ClientCredentials> class when a client sends a SOAP message and a <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken> security token is needed.
trans-unit.target: O <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A>método é chamado pelo <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ClientCredentials>classe quando um cliente envia uma mensagem SOAP e um <xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken>token de segurança é necessária.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Tokens.KerberosRequestorSecurityToken> </xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ClientCredentials> </xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A> method calls the GetTokenCore method.
trans-unit.target: O <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A>método chama o método GetTokenCore.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.SecurityTokenProvider.GetToken%2A>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.TimeSpan> that specifies the timeout value for the message that gets the security token.
trans-unit.target: Um <xref:System.TimeSpan>que especifica o valor de tempo limite para a mensagem que obtém o token de segurança.</xref:System.TimeSpan>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.IdentityModel.Tokens.SecurityToken"></xref> that represents the security token to get.
trans-unit.target: O <xref href="System.IdentityModel.Tokens.SecurityToken"> </xref> que representa o token de segurança para obter.

trans-unit.source: When the value of the NetworkCredential property is `null` and the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.KerberosSecurityTokenProvider.GetTokenCore%2A> method is called, the current context of the calling thread (<xref:System.Net.CredentialCache.DefaultNetworkCredentials%2A>) is used as a client identity.
trans-unit.target: Quando o valor da propriedade NetworkCredential é `null` e <xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.KerberosSecurityTokenProvider.GetTokenCore%2A>método é chamado, o contexto atual do thread de chamada (<xref:System.Net.CredentialCache.DefaultNetworkCredentials%2A>) é usado como uma identidade de cliente.</xref:System.Net.CredentialCache.DefaultNetworkCredentials%2A> </xref:System.IdentityModel.Selectors.KerberosSecurityTokenProvider.GetTokenCore%2A>
